Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

> If you have a toaster oven, feel free to skip preheating—you'll use it to
> toast the buns in step 3.

Wash and dry all produce.

Trim and halve @Persian cucumber{1}(halved lengthwise); slice crosswise into
¼-inch-thick half-moons.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss together cucumber, @shredded red cabbage{4%oz},
@rice wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @sugar{1 1/2%tsp}, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}.
Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

Tear @pulled pork{8%oz} into smaller pieces if necessary.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #medium pan{} over medium heat.
Add pork and cook, stirring, until warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @bulgogi sauce{4%oz} and @water{1/4%cup}. Bring to a boil, then reduce
heat to low. Simmer until saucy, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} with @Sriracha{1%tsp}
to taste. Season with @salt and @pepper to taste.

Place @butter{1%tbsp} in a separate #small microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave until
melted, ~{30-40%seconds}.

Halve @brioche buns{2}. Brush melted butter onto cut sides.

Place cut sides up directly on oven rack (or in a #toaster oven{}) and toast
until golden brown, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Divide buns between plates; spread Sriracha mayo onto cut sides of top buns.
Fill buns with pork and a bit of slaw. Serve with remaining slaw on the side.